# Fix pnpm Installation Issue

The objective is to update the [start_all.bat](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip/start_all.bat) script to use `npx pnpm` as a fallback when a global `pnpm` installation is missing or fails.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component Name]
Update the startup script in the root directory.

#### [MODIFY] [start_all.bat](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip/start_all.bat)
- Detect if `pnpm` is in PATH.
- If not, check for [npm](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip/scripts/dev-runner.mjs#248-281) and use `npx pnpm` for all commands.
- This avoids permission issues related to global installs.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Run the [.bat](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/paperclip/start_all.bat) file in an environment where `pnpm` is not installed.
- Ensure it successfully runs `npx pnpm install` and `npx pnpm dev`.
